Package model

package model
The model package contains the classes that represent the data and database interactions for the KYI Integrated application. These classes encapsulate the core data structures and operations on them.

Key classes:

  • DatabaseConnector - Manages database connection and operations.
  • Station - Represents a station entity.
  • StationDAO - Defines data access methods for stations.

  • Class
    Description
    Admin
    Represents an admin user in the system.
    DatabaseConnector
    Manages the connection and operations with the MySQL database.
    Passenger
    The Passenger class represents a passenger in the KYI Integrated system.
    PassengerDAO
    The PassengerDAO interface provides methods for performing database operations related to passengers in the KYI Integrated system.
    Station
    The Station class represents a railway station in the KYI Integrated system.
    StationDAO
    The StationDAO interface provides methods for accessing and manipulating station data in the database.
    Ticket
    The Ticket class represents a ticket in the system.
    TicketDAO
    The TicketDAO interface provides methods for performing operations on ticket data in the database.
    Train
    The Train class represents a train with its details such as train ID, name, starting station, ending station, departing and arriving times, and price.
    TrainDAO
    The TrainDAO interface provides methods for accessing and manipulating train data in the database.
    User
    Represents a user in the system.
    UserDAO
    Interface for User Data Access Object (DAO).
